## Strategy Comparison

**Reference Strategy**: Optimizes by precomputing the reciprocal to avoid division, but maintains the two-call approach for precision.

**Proposed Strategy**: Changes the algorithm fundamentally by using only one random call, sacrificing precision for speed. This is a **different optimization strategy** from the reference.

The reference maintains the dual-call approach for precision while optimizing division; the proposal changes the algorithm to single-call. Even though both precompute the reciprocal, the core algorithmic approach differs significantly.

## Final Verdict

The proposed optimization uses a different algorithmic strategy (single random call vs. dual calls for precision) than the reference solution, even though both share the reciprocal precomputation optimization.